Job Description:
Mid-Level Civil Engineer

MS&K Engineering, a Civil Engineering firm, has an opening for a Civil Engineer to join our team in Bennington, Vermont. The successful candidate will have demonstrated experience in civil engineering and will be tasked with designing and permitting residential, commercial, institutional, and municipal projects of varying scope and scale. Individuals must possess a strong work ethic and a professional demeanor. The successful candidate must be willing to perform both office and field work.

Qualifications:
Bachelors degree in Civil Engineering from an accredited college is required;
EIT Registration;
Two to four years of professional experience.
Responsibilities:
Perform standard civil engineering design calculations and quantity estimates;
Draft plans and specifications under the supervision of a Professional Engineer;
Produce detailed and finished drawings by making revisions from senior project team members comments and plans;
Prepare construction documents for submittal to clients, municipalities, agencies and others as directed;
Prepare environmental permit applications and associated plans and exhibits;
Administration of construction phase services, including field observation, preparation of pay applications and change orders, and construction coordination;
Work in a team environment on various projects and tasks, including storm water, water, sanitary sewer and site development;
Develop reports and preliminary concepts;
Resolve design and construction issues.
Skills & Knowledge:
Must have working knowledge and understanding of basic geometry and trigonometry;
Basic knowledge of land survey and civil engineering terms and practices;
Extremely detail oriented;
Familiarity with construction standards and terminology;
Ability to understand and follow written and verbal instructions;
Ability to work independently on complex projects with general direction;
Demonstrated ability to handle multiple projects simultaneously;
Ability to work in a team environment;
Strong organizational, analytical and problem-solving skills;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills;
Proficiency with AutoCAD Civil 3D and Mircorsoft Office Suite is required;Proficiency with hydraulic/hydrologic stormwater modeling software (HydroCAD or similar) preferred.
MSK offers a full benefits package, including health insurance, paid leave, matching retirement contributions, life insurance and a competitive salary, depending on experience and qualifications.

Job Type: Full-time

Experience:
Civil Engineering: 2 years (Required)
Education:
Bachelor's (Required)
